post.message:
**IMMINENT THREAT WARNING**

HUMINT reports suicide bomber intercepted at outer checkpoint. Possible additional threats in crowd.

@crisis_command_group Recommend halting pedestrian processing immediately.

Convoy 1 safe at airport. Loading C-17 despite weather hold.

@all_evacuation_personnel Final embassy elements departing via helo. All remaining personnel to airport immediately.

This is Ambassador Mitchell - Godspeed to all. See you at the airport.

C-130 on final approach. Tactical landing authorized.

Ground crews report sporadic small arms fire near runway. Combat landing required.

@evacuation_ops_team Have next 150 ready to board immediately on landing.

Predator feed shows insurgent columns entering city outskirts.

Main force approximately 30 minutes from airport perimeter.

@crisis_command_group Recommend immediate departure all remaining aircraft.

Final convoy taking heavy fire 2km from airport.

Apaches inbound to provide cover. Danger close authorization requested.

@michael.brennan Keep pushing! Almost home!

C-130 departing! 147 souls aboard.

That's our last bird before the storm hits. All remaining evacuees will need to wait it out.

@jennifer.park Any chance of rotary wing?

All remaining aircraft grounded by weather.

@all_evacuation_personnel We hold the airport until conditions improve. No one fights alone.

Gen. Carter - what's our defensive situation?

All convoy personnel accounted for and under cover.

Terminal building secured. Establishing defensive positions at all entry points.

@security_forces Need ammunition redistribution. Running 30% on all weapons.

B-52s requesting final confirmation. Strikes will be danger close - 500m from terminal.

All personnel need to be in hardened cover NOW.

@james.carter Your authorization needed.

Picking up emergency beacon from downed pilot 3km north.

Apache crew alive but surrounded. Requesting immediate SAR.

@michael.brennan Can your team attempt rescue?

B-52 strike in 60 seconds. Everyone down!

@all_evacuation_personnel When this is over, we'll have a window to evacuate. Stay ready.

Proud to serve with all of you.

Clearing emergency runway with vehicles. 1,000 meters usable.

C-17 will need combat approach and immediate departure.

@evacuation_ops_team Stage everyone at gate 3. NOW!

FLASH - Mortar team setting up 1km east!

They're targeting the aircraft! Need immediate suppression!

@marcus.jones Can you engage?

CENTCOM sends:

'Magnificent work under impossible conditions. Every service member showed extraordinary valor. Welcome home.'

@all_evacuation_personnel Stand down from alert. Mission accomplished.

**CRISIS DAY 1 - 0600L**

Situation deteriorating rapidly. Activating embassy evacuation plan.

@james.carter Need Marine reinforcements ASAP
@elena.volkov What's the threat timeline?

All gates secured. Implementing 100% ID checks.

Local staff extremely nervous. Many requesting immediate evacuation.

@lisa.thompson Need guidance on local employee evacuation criteria.

Military command fragmenting. Some units joining insurgents.

My battalion remains loyal but for how long? Need extraction guarantees for my men.

@sarah.mitchell Can you confirm?

Police checkpoints cooperating so far. My units providing convoy escort.

Hearing radio chatter about planned ambushes tomorrow. Stay alert.

@route-security Pass to convoy commanders.

Crowd building at main gate. Maybe 500 people.

Mostly visa applicants and local staff families. Peaceful so far but desperate.

@lisa.thompson Need crowd control guidance.

First convoy attack. Casualties inbound.

Insurgents getting bolder. Dawn assault looking certain.

@sarah.mitchell Recommend final evacuation wave NOW.

All reserves to north perimeter!

This is the big one. Hold the line!

@michael.brennan Get your QRF moving!

Marines report movement in surrounding buildings.

Definitely surveillance. They're watching our pattern.

@convoy-ops Recommend maximum route variation.
